The paper deals with the complexity of the valued constraint satisfaction problem (VCSP), which is a fundamental problem in computer science and optimization. The paper introduces a new class of tractable VCSPs based on a generalization of submodularity, which is a concept in discrete mathematics and optimization. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) categories. The paper also discusses the use of graph-based techniques and reduction techniques, which are common in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with combinatorial optimization, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
